  "text": "GCC's optimization pass registration and execution follows a well-structured pipeline defined across five critical files:\n\n1. **Pass Definition and Registration (gcc/passes.def)**: This file defines the master execution order of all optimization passes using the NEXT_PASS macro. For example, dead code elimination passes are registered with `NEXT_PASS(pass_dce)` at multiple points in the compilation pipeline (lowering, optimization, and code generation phases). The file uses INSERT_PASSES_AFTER and TERMINATE_PASS_LIST macros to organize passes into five distinct lists: all_lowering_passes, all_small_ipa_passes, all_regular_ipa_passes, all_late_ipa_passes, and all_passes.\n\n2. **Pass Manager Interface (gcc/pass_manager.h)**: Defines the `class pass_manager` (line 47) which orchestrates pass execution. The pass_manager maintains five opt_pass* pointers for each pass list and generates individual pass member variables through macro expansion of pass-instances.def. Key methods include register_pass(), register_dump_files(), get_pass_for_id(), and register_pass_name(). The file also defines the base class opt_pass interface and uses macro definitions to declaratively generate pass member fields.\n\n3. **Pass Manager Implementation (gcc/passes.cc)**: Implements the pass_manager constructor (line 1577) which processes passes.def to build the pass tree by creating pass instances through make_pass_* factory functions. The critical execution function `execute_one_pass()` (line 2579) handles gate checking (virtual method), pass execution, and TODO flag processing. It manages pass context switching and profiles pass performance. The pass_manager traverses the pass tree and executes sub-passes recursively.\n\n4. **Tree-SSA Pass Header (gcc/tree-pass.h)**: Defines the opt_pass base class (line 73) with virtual methods gate() and execute() that all concrete passes override. Defines `struct pass_data` (line 40) containing pass metadata (type, name, properties_required, properties_provided, flags). Declares specialized pass classes: `class gimple_opt_pass` (line 116), `class rtl_opt_pass` (line 126), `class ipa_opt_pass_d` (line 141), and `class simple_ipa_opt_pass` (line 197). Declares external factory functions like `extern gimple_opt_pass *make_pass_dce()` (line 412).\n\n5. **Concrete Example: Dead Code Elimination (gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc)**: Implements DCE as a concrete GIMPLE pass. Defines `const pass_data pass_data_dce` (line 2038) with GIMPLE_PASS type and SSA properties. Implements three classes: `class pass_dce_base` (line 2051) providing common DCE logic, `class pass_dce` (line 2082) for standard DCE, and `class pass_cd_dce` (line 2121) for control-dependent DCE. Each class implements gate() to check flag_tree_dce and execute() to call perform_tree_ssa_dce(). Factory functions `make_pass_dce()` (line 2101) and `make_pass_cd_dce()` (line 2140) create pass instances.\n\nExecution flow: passes.def defines pass order → pass_manager constructor reads passes.def macro definitions → factory functions (make_pass_dce) instantiate passes → pass_manager maintains pass tree → execute_one_pass() gates and executes each pass → opt_pass::execute() runs concrete optimization logic. This design enables pass reordering via configuration, selective pass enablement through gates, and modular optimization pass development."
}

